{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17503548","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17503548"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:02:59+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:02:59+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2042"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2042","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2042"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.15,0.09,0.54,0.16,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2042"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92432"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2042","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2042"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2042"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75754"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"37"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1027"},{"type":"tags","id":"2038"},{"type":"tags","id":"2182"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4971"},{"type":"tags","id":"5178"},{"type":"tags","id":"11632"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"31622"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31623"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42442"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44670"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92432","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/92432"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 25-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with concerns about sexual dysfunction. He reports difficulty maintaining erections and decreased libido for the last two months. He has a history of major depressive disorder and started an antidepressant around the same time his symptoms began. He has no other medical conditions and takes no other regular medications. He exercises regularly and maintains a healthy diet. On examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. His body mass index is 20 kg/m\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following antidepressants is most appropriate to minimise sexual dysfunction?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Sertraline","Clomipramine","Mirtazapine","Fluoxetine","Phenelzine"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with antidepressant-induced sexual dysfunction, a common side effect that can significantly impact quality of life and medication adherence. The choice of antidepressant should balance therapeutic efficacy with minimising side effects.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMirtazapine\u003C/strong\u003E has a unique mechanism of action as a noradrenergic and specific serotonergic antidepressant (NaSSA). It has a lower incidence of sexual dysfunction compared to other antidepressants, making it an appropriate choice for this patient. Its main side effects include sedation and weight gain, which should be monitored.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESertraline\u003C/strong\u003E, as a selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor (SSRI), commonly causes sexual dysfunction including decreased libido, delayed ejaculation, and erectile dysfunction. These effects are thought to be related to increased serotonin levels. \u003Cstrong\u003EFluoxetine\u003C/strong\u003E, another SSRI, has similar sexual side effects to sertraline. Its long half-life means these effects can persist even after discontinuation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EClomipramine\u003C/strong\u003E, a tricyclic antidepressant, has a high incidence of sexual dysfunction due to its strong serotonergic and anticholinergic effects. It can cause erectile dysfunction, decreased libido, and anorgasmia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPhenelzine\u003C/strong\u003E, a monoamine oxidase inhibitor (MAOI), can cause significant sexual dysfunction and has additional risks requiring dietary restrictions and multiple drug interactions.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Mirtazapine has a lower incidence of sexual dysfunction compared to other antidepressants due to its unique mechanism of action.","Sexual dysfunction is a common side effect of selective serotonin reuptake inhibitors (SSRIs) and can significantly impact medication adherence.","When selecting antidepressants, consider both the therapeutic benefit and potential impact on quality of life including sexual function."],"references":["Serretti A, Chiesa A. Treatment-Emergent Sexual Dysfunction Related to Antidepressants. Journal of Clinical Psychopharmacology. 2009;29(3):259-266. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19440080/","Montgomery S. Safety of mirtazapine: a review. International Clinical Psychopharmacology. 1995;10(Supplement 4):37-45. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/8930008/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75754"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2042"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75754","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/75754"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-17T19:33:57+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-17T19:33:58+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2042"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92432"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"10","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/10"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udfad","name":"Psychiatry","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-